---
# Checks: bugprone-*, performance-*, concurrency-*, modernize-* (minus trailing-return-type),
# readability-* (minus the noisy ones listed below).
#
# Exclusions and justifications:
#   - modernize-use-trailing-return-type: C++20 with traditional signatures reads better
#     in a codebase already written that way. Enforcing consistency would require a mass
#     rewrite that doesn't improve clarity.
#   - readability-identifier-length: Project uses single-letter loop indices (i, j)
#     which are idiomatic and clear in context. Short names for temporary vars are fine.
#   - readability-magic-numbers: Crypto nonces, chunk sizes, buffer lengths are by
#     definition "magic" constants — they come from specs/standards. Named constants
#     exist where appropriate (VIDEO_CHUNK_SIZE, KEY_SIZE, etc.); flagging all of them
#     would create noise.
#   - readability-function-cognitive-complexity: Classes like Vault, GalleryGrid have
#     legitimate complexity from state machines and UI event dispatch. Artificial
#     refactoring to pass this check would reduce readability.

Checks: >
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  concurrency-*,
  modernize-*,
  -modernize-use-trailing-return-type,
  readability-*,
  -readability-identifier-length,
  -readability-magic-numbers,
  -readability-function-cognitive-complexity

WarningsAsErrors: ''

# HeaderFilterRegex: Only check src/ headers, not vendor or tests.
# Vendor headers (third-party code) and test fixtures are out of scope for
# style/modernization linting — we enforce practices only on our own code.
HeaderFilterRegex: '^.*/src/.*'

# Common config
UseColor: true
